Replying to 
@nithyavramanThe City Council has recently created a $100 million renter relief fund. This is a great start. But even they know it isn't nearly enough.

That’s why the fund has been set up as a lottery, where some families will get help and others get nothing.

Replying to 
@nithyavramanCases and hospitalizations began rising shortly after indoor dining reopened.

Instead of taking a step back to re-evaluate the pace of resuming business, we went ahead and reopened bars -- this time with one day of notice.

We talked to L.A. City Council candidate 
@nithyavraman
 and Meghan Choi from 
@GroundGameLA
 about how they’re building “resilient neighborhoods” through their people-powered campaign.Building Neighborhood Power
forgeorganizing.org

